  "text": "The second annual Libby Awards were just announced last week. If you’re unfamiliar, Libby is the library reading app by Overdrive. It’s used in over 22,000 public libraries and has over one billion checkouts. In other words, Libby has a very unique perspective when it comes to reading habits and books, which is why looking at their list of the biggest books of March is so interesting. Unsurprisingly, their list has some of the same ones we mentioned in our own March roundup—there’s the fifth entry into Suzanne Collins’s mega-bestselling Hunger Games series, and the third in Tracy Deonn’s Legendborn Cycle series. There’s also new nonfiction by John Green, and a new fantasy novella by Amal El-Mohtar, who co-wrote the book that had thee Bigolas Dickolas in a chokehold. Continue below for those books and more. Sunrise on the Reaping (The Hunger Games #5) by Suzanne Collins Everything Is Tuberculosis by John Green Oathbound (The Legendborn Cycle #3) by Tracy Deonn The River Has Roots by Amal El-Mohtar Count My Lies by Sophie Stava Wild Dark Shore by Charlotte McConaghy The Buffalo Hunter Hunter by Stephen Graham Jones The Dream Hotel by Laila Lalami They Bloom at Night by Trang Thanh Tran Saving Five by Amanda Nguyen The Scorpion and the Night by Amélie Wen Zhao Harriet Tubman by Bob the Drag Queen For the full list, visit Libby. Find more news and stories of interest from the book world in Breaking in Books.",
